00026 /*
00027  * This header file defines the data structures sent by the VM
00028  * through the JVMTI CompiledMethodLoad callback function via the
00029  * "void * compile_info" parameter. The memory pointed to by the
00030  * compile_info parameter may not be referenced after returning from
00031  * the CompiledMethodLoad callback. These are VM implementation
00032  * specific data structures that may evolve in future releases. A
00033  * JVMTI agent should interpret a non-NULL compile_info as a pointer
00034  * to a region of memory containing a list of records. In a typical
00035  * usage scenario, a JVMTI agent would cast each record to a
00036  * jvmtiCompiledMethodLoadRecordHeader, a struct that represents
00037  * arbitrary information. This struct contains a kind field to indicate
00038  * the kind of information being passed, and a pointer to the next
00039  * record. If the kind field indicates inlining information, then the
00040  * agent would cast the record to a jvmtiCompiledMethodLoadInlineRecord.
00041  * This record contains an array of PCStackInfo structs, which indicate
00042  * for every pc address what are the methods on the invocation stack.
00043  * The "methods" and "bcis" fields in each PCStackInfo struct specify a
00044  * 1-1 mapping between these inlined methods and their bytecode indices.
00045  * This can be used to derive the proper source lines of the inlined
00046  * methods.
00047  */
00048

00070 /*
00071  * Record that represents arbitrary information passed through JVMTI
00072  * CompiledMethodLoadEvent void pointer.
00073  */
00074 typedef struct _jvmtiCompiledMethodLoadRecordHeader {
00075   jvmtiCMLRKind kind;     /* id for the kind of info passed in the record */
00076   jint majorinfoversion;  /* major and minor info version values. Init'ed */
00077   jint minorinfoversion;  /* to current version value in jvmtiExport.cpp. */
00078 
00079   struct _jvmtiCompiledMethodLoadRecordHeader* next;
00080 } jvmtiCompiledMethodLoadRecordHeader;

00082 /*
00083  * Record that gives information about the methods on the compile-time
00084  * stack at a specific pc address of a compiled method. Each element in
00085  * the methods array maps to same element in the bcis array.
00086  */
00087 typedef struct _PCStackInfo {
00088   void* pc;             /* the pc address for this compiled method */
00089   jint numstackframes;  /* number of methods on the stack */
00090   jmethodID* methods;   /* array of numstackframes method ids */
00091   jint* bcis;           /* array of numstackframes bytecode indices */
00092 } PCStackInfo;
00093 
00094 /*
00095  * Record that contains inlining information for each pc address of
00096  * an nmethod.
00097  */
00098 typedef struct _jvmtiCompiledMethodLoadInlineRecord {
00099   jvmtiCompiledMethodLoadRecordHeader header;  /* common header for casting */
00100   jint numpcs;          /* number of pc descriptors in this nmethod */
00101   PCStackInfo* pcinfo;  /* array of numpcs pc descriptors */
00102 } jvmtiCompiledMethodLoadInlineRecord;
